<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-02T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-02T19:00:00-05:00" n="280" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1124.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-02T19:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 2, 1914, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 31, 11 p.m. Give what dates in your opinion primary and
                            general elections will be held. Is Constitutional Congress still in
                            session? If so, when will it finish its labors?</p>
                        <p>In your utterances you will use caution when speaking of the coming
                            elections and the candidates. The United States has no interest except
                            to aid in the election of the candidate desired by the voters through
                            the medium of free and fair means.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>